# Component Patterns & Styling Guidelines

## Component Architecture

### shadcn/ui Components
- Use shadcn/ui components from [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/) as base building blocks
- All UI components follow the shadcn/ui pattern with `cn()` utility for className merging
- Components use `React.forwardRef` for proper ref forwarding
- Use `class-variance-authority` (cva) for variant-based styling

### Component Structure
```tsx
// Standard component pattern
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

interface ComponentProps {
  className?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Component({ className, children, ...props }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn("base-styles", className)} {...props}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Styling Guidelines

### Tailwind CSS v4
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 with custom design system defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- CSS variables are defined for consistent theming (light/dark mode)
- Use semantic color tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, etc.

### Color System
- Primary colors: `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`
- Secondary colors: `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary-foreground`
- Muted colors: `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`
- Accent colors: `bg-accent`, `text-accent-foreground`
- Destructive colors: `bg-destructive`, `text-destructive-foreground`

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach with responsive breakpoints
- Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` prefixes for responsive styles
- Common patterns: `px-6 sm:px-8 md:px-10` for horizontal padding

### Animation & Motion
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Use `tw-animate-css` for simple CSS animations
- Common animation classes: `animate-fade-in`, `animate-slide-up`

